/**
@page source_separation Source Separation

sherpa-onnx supports source separation through the
@ref SherpaOnnxCreateOfflineSourceSeparation() API. Configure exactly one
model family by filling in the corresponding field of
@ref SherpaOnnxOfflineSourceSeparationModelConfig.

@see SherpaOnnxCreateOfflineSourceSeparation,
     SherpaOnnxOfflineSourceSeparationConfig

@tableofcontents

@section ss_spleeter Spleeter

Spleeter separates audio into vocals and accompaniment (2 stems).

@code
SherpaOnnxOfflineSourceSeparationConfig config;
memset(&config, 0, sizeof(config));
config.model.spleeter.vocals =
    "./sherpa-onnx-spleeter-2stems-fp16/vocals.fp16.onnx";
config.model.spleeter.accompaniment =
    "./sherpa-onnx-spleeter-2stems-fp16/accompaniment.fp16.onnx";
config.model.num_threads = 1;
config.model.provider = "cpu";

const SherpaOnnxOfflineSourceSeparation *ss =
    SherpaOnnxCreateOfflineSourceSeparation(&config);
// ... use ss ...
SherpaOnnxDestroyOfflineSourceSeparation(ss);
@endcode

Model package: `sherpa-onnx-spleeter-2stems-fp16`

Example source: [source-separation-spleeter-c-api.c](https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx/blob/master/c-api-examples/source-separation-spleeter-c-api.c)

@section ss_uvr UVR (MDX-Net)

UVR separates audio into vocals and non-vocals.

@code
SherpaOnnxOfflineSourceSeparationConfig config;
memset(&config, 0, sizeof(config));
config.model.uvr.model = "./UVR-MDX-NET-Voc_FT.onnx";
config.model.num_threads = 1;
config.model.provider = "cpu";

const SherpaOnnxOfflineSourceSeparation *ss =
    SherpaOnnxCreateOfflineSourceSeparation(&config);
// ... use ss ...
SherpaOnnxDestroyOfflineSourceSeparation(ss);
@endcode

Model file: `UVR-MDX-NET-Voc_FT.onnx`

Example source: [source-separation-uvr-c-api.c](https://github.com/k2-fsa/sherpa-onnx/blob/master/c-api-examples/source-separation-uvr-c-api.c)
*/
